Thought: To check if a number is prime, we need to see if it has any divisors other than 1 and itself. We can do this by checking for divisibility from 2 up to the square root of the number.

```ruby
def is_prime?(num)
  return false if num <= 1 # Numbers less than or equal to 1 are not prime
  
  (2..Math.sqrt(num)).none? { |i| num % i == 0 }
end
```
